a challenge to get new business let alone to compete against other MRO suppliers. Closing down a distribution center, minimizing the product lines, and the corporate downsizing only says one thing "Business For Sale"...Losing strategic accounts hurts the reps abilities to land the "Large Accounts" and the competitive edge to the big guys. There is currently no "career ladder" unless you just want to be a sales rep and slowly grow your own business.Advice to ManagementYou should have never gotten rid of a great sales leader. He really motivated the sales teams! Rethink the growth process and put "true" sales leaders in charge of the sales teams and not an accountant. The current path looks like the end of the Dinosaurs...Couldn't adapt and became extinct!Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (0) Lawson Products Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Lawson Products 2017-07-11 06:36 PDT Jun 14, 2017"Good Luck...."StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Sales RepresentativeCurrent Employee - Sales RepresentativeDoesn't RecommendNegative OutlookApproves of CEOI have been working at Lawson Products full-time (More than a year)Prosgreat work and life balanceConscompanies greedy and charges customer way, way, way to muchAdvice to ManagementHelp your salesmen to be better salesmen, and manage. Give your Reps someone to count on and help them be better than they are.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (0) Lawson Products Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Lawson Products 2017-06-14 20:57 PDT May 19, 2017 Helpful (1)"Great Company"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Team Lead in Chicago, ILCurrent Employee - Team Lead 