hey want to take the company in. They are constantly hiring new reps which only floods the territories, along with it seeming like there are thousand things about the company but you only know what your manager wants you to know. Company seems to want to be more price-competitive are the reps expense, i.e. less commissions. You use your own car, pay for your own gas, and they require you to carry boat loads of insurance on your own vehicle which costs you even more money.Advice to ManagementPick a direction and stick to it. Let all of your reps know the ins and outs of the company, it will only help then gain more business which will in turn help the company. It's one thing if you want to be more competitive and charge less for a product but the company should take a hit along with your reps... they're the ones that can't afford it.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (2) Lawson Products Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Lawson Products 2017-02-27 15:15 PST Feb 8, 2017 Helpful (2)"Pricing Analyst"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementFormer Employee - Pricing Analyst in Chicago, ILFormer Employee - Pricing Analyst in Chicago, ILDoesn't RecommendNeutral OutlookNo opinion of CEOI worked at Lawson Products full-time (More than 5 years)ProsGreat direct team, always worked well together and got along great. Hard working team, good work family. Everyone helped each other to get the job doneConsBoys club. Sometimes in the area or the other groups you were working with it seemed your opinion didn't matter or you had to prove yourself because you were not a manAdvice to ManagementPay attention to the little guysShare on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (2) Lawson Products Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Lawson Product